  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment (W-EP-01 adversarial)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under ventricular assist device (VAD) conditions. COU2 evaluates whether the computational model can predict absolute hemolysis levels for a Class III VAD device at Model Risk Level 5. This synthetic adversarial package embeds an orphan claim (W-EP-01): the claim node referenced by bindsClaim carries a plausible statement about hemolysis prediction adequacy but has no prov:wasDerivedFrom link to any evidence node, rendering it unsupported. Evidence items are discussed in the validation results but are not structurally connected to the claim.",
